    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-05-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-05-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 23,
                                1890</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that a
                            statement having appeared in the newspapers to the effect that the
                            United States revenue cruisers have received orders to proceed to
                            Behring Sea for the purpose of preventing the exercise of the seal
                            fishery by foreign vessels in non-territorial waters, and that statement
                            having been confirmed yesterday by you, lam instructed by the Marquis of
                            Salisbury to state to you that a formal protest by Her Majesty’s
                            Government against any such interference with British vessels will be
                            forwarded to you without delay.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
